by @drewtrush // Grosvenor Arch is located in Grand Staircase- Escalante National Monument.  Orginally named Butler Arch, it was renamed in 1947 by members of a National Geographic Expedition to one of the last unexplored regions in the U.S. at the time, the Desert Southwest.  Gilbert Grosvenor was the first full time editor of National Geographic Magazine. It is a unique double arch standing almost 150 above the desert floor.  Well worth the drive. •••••
Grand Staircase-Escalante is just one of the National Monuments that has come under review by the Trump administration.  You can learn more by clicking on the link in my bio. #utah #publiclands #grandstaircaseescalante #nationalmonument

I've tried to get a permit for "The Wave" on 10 different occasions in the past 6 months... if any of you have entered the Wave lottery you know how terrible of an experience it is. Dozens of people crammed into a little room with about a 1% chance of getting the prize. But, not winning the lottery has been the biggest blessing in disguise. Every time I lose it gives me time to to go out and explore the surrounding area. Constantly blown away by the lesser known gems out there.

Behind The Album: "OG Malone" - Episode 2! My up-coming and debut album is conceptualized by 5 of my favorite passions: lifestyle, education, exploration, sports and vintage fashion within the Rocky Mountains. I moved to Utah in May 2014.  Went on my first tour in May 2015. Became a booking agent in January 2016. And since then, I've helped book 15+ events in Utah. One of my first bookings was bringing 2Chainz to Provo, UT. I learned that you have to diversify your brand, your network, your connections and your hustles and simultaneously channel them to one fluid direction. Being from Atlanta, and having the opportunity to bring 2Chainz to Provo, a city that impacted me in such a positive way, has helped me develop my go getter mentality. I realized that just because people say something can't be done or that it never happened before, doesn't mean you can't make it happen. Much love to @aarondelro, Double A MGMT, The Onus Brand, Chad, Street Execs, Knoah, 2Chainz, DJ ESudd and everyone else that helped make this happen. Being able to make events like these happen behind the scenes has inspired me with the creative process of my debut album. Much love to everyone who's been apart of the wave. ⠀
